The paper deals with learning graph representations from noisy, multi-source data, which is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on community detection, which is a subfield of network science and graph theory, and can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD). The paper also deals with incorporating partial information from different data sources, which is a problem that falls under the category of data integration and fusion (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a boosting-inspired framework, which is a machine learning technique that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
